26
00:02:45,160 --> 00:02:46,520
-Did you call his guardian?
-No.

27
00:02:47,440 --> 00:02:49,040
Please call...

28
00:02:50,320 --> 00:02:51,560
Professor Jo Gi-bum.

29
00:02:53,480 --> 00:02:55,560
The receiver cannot be reached.
You will be directed...

30
00:02:59,560 --> 00:03:00,800
Hello?

31
00:03:03,760 --> 00:03:05,200
Which hospital is it?

32
00:03:22,720 --> 00:03:27,200
(Episode 12: To Die or To Be Mad)

33
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:31,280
(Bureau Chief, Na Ha-young)

34
00:03:31,360 --> 00:03:33,200
(Lee Hyeong-du)

35
00:03:36,079 --> 00:03:37,120
Hello?

36
00:03:37,120 --> 00:03:38,960
Seok-du has disappeared.

37
00:03:40,720 --> 00:03:42,880
They made a move before us.

38
00:03:42,880 --> 00:03:44,000
Find him!

39
00:03:59,320 --> 00:04:02,480
Isn't this Ma Dong-chan's phone?

40
00:04:02,480 --> 00:04:05,040
Yes, it is. I'm a nurse.

41
00:04:05,040 --> 00:04:07,120
He's hospitalized.

42
00:04:08,040 --> 00:04:09,880
He's hospitalized?

43
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:30,880
The toxins are accumulating in your body.

44
00:04:30,880 --> 00:04:32,280
That's why you were in shock.

45
00:04:32,560 --> 00:04:34,240
This is a temporary antidote.

46
00:04:34,240 --> 00:04:36,520
The symptom will manifest itself
once again in 48 hours.

47
00:04:37,159 --> 00:04:40,640
But this antidote won't work
the second time around.

48
00:04:40,880 --> 00:04:42,440
48 hours?

49
00:04:45,680 --> 00:04:47,080
Then...

50
00:04:47,560 --> 00:04:50,159
will Mi-ran also suffer from this?

51
00:04:50,560 --> 00:04:51,600
Yes.

52
00:04:51,840 --> 00:04:54,200
There has been a variation in the LAP...

53
00:04:54,200 --> 00:04:56,000
and has turned into toxins.

54
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:58,560
Professor Hwang had mentioned this
in his note.

55
00:04:58,720 --> 00:05:00,800
He already knew this would happen.

56
00:05:00,880 --> 00:05:03,880
However, we do not have a reagent
that will get rid of it permanently.

57
00:05:04,360 --> 00:05:06,920
I'm currently researching the protocol.

58
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:10,160
But I need Professor Hwang's help.

59
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:11,720
I need to know the code...

60
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:14,280
for the LAP that he administered
into your bodies.

61
00:05:14,360 --> 00:05:16,280
Where is he right now?

62
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:21,840
Are you okay?

63
00:05:21,920 --> 00:05:24,000
What happened? Did you get a fever again?

64
00:05:24,680 --> 00:05:26,000
Are you okay?

65
00:05:26,640 --> 00:05:28,080
I'm fine.

66
00:05:32,720 --> 00:05:33,960
What is this?

67
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:39,080
When did I get this bruise?

68
00:05:39,080 --> 00:05:40,440
That isn't a bruise.

69
00:05:42,720 --> 00:05:43,720
Then?

70
00:05:43,720 --> 00:05:45,920
I think the variation is happening
in your body as well.

71
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:47,480
We'll have to keep an eye on it.

72
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:49,040
Could this be...

73
00:05:49,680 --> 00:05:51,800
lethal?

74
00:05:53,680 --> 00:05:55,480
I need to see Professor Hwang right now.

75
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:58,600
That's the problem. I cannot reach him.

76
00:05:59,240 --> 00:06:01,800
And he said something strange.

77
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:03,640
He said he trusted me.

78
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:10,240
-What are you doing?
-I need to find him.

79
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:11,320
There's no time.

80
00:06:11,320 --> 00:06:13,480
You just collapsed. You need to rest.

81
00:06:13,520 --> 00:06:16,040
You must remain at the hospital
so we can keep an eye on you.

82
00:06:16,280 --> 00:06:18,040
I'll look for him.

83
00:06:18,560 --> 00:06:20,120
Go home.

84
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:22,440
How can I?

85
00:06:23,480 --> 00:06:25,560
You must protect your immune system,

86
00:06:25,560 --> 00:06:26,960
so go home.

87
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:31,120
Since when did you have this?

88
00:06:31,720 --> 00:06:32,800
I wasn't aware of it.

89
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:34,320
How is it possible that you didn't know?

90
00:06:34,320 --> 00:06:36,159
There's something wrong on your arm.

91
00:06:39,680 --> 00:06:42,040
Go home and rest.

92
00:06:42,320 --> 00:06:43,720
I won't go.

93
00:06:43,720 --> 00:06:46,120
-Go.
-No.

94
00:06:55,080 --> 00:06:56,480
Professor Jo Gi-bum?

95
00:06:59,280 --> 00:07:02,200
Can you spare me a minute?

96
00:07:05,560 --> 00:07:06,960
Are those two...

97
00:07:07,640 --> 00:07:09,040
in danger?

98
00:07:09,040 --> 00:07:11,320
I need to find Professor Hwang.

99
00:07:11,320 --> 00:07:16,160
Is Professor Hwang the only one
who can cure them?

100
00:07:16,160 --> 00:07:18,160
I'm currently looking for a solution.

101
00:07:22,800 --> 00:07:24,600
Where's Lee Seok-du?

102
00:07:30,880 --> 00:07:32,880
Why are you asking me that?

103
00:07:33,159 --> 00:07:35,120
Dong-chan told me.

104
00:07:35,400 --> 00:07:37,040
He told me that the current Lee Seok-du...

105
00:07:37,040 --> 00:07:39,800
isn't really him
and that the real Lee Seok-du...

106
00:07:40,800 --> 00:07:42,840
has been in a capsule.

107
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:47,680
Now, can you believe that...

108
00:07:48,960 --> 00:07:50,320
we're on the same team?

109
00:07:51,680 --> 00:07:53,960
Go home. I'll call a cab.

110
00:07:53,960 --> 00:07:56,000
Why are you trying to send me away?

111
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:58,280
Your being here won't help me.

112
00:07:58,280 --> 00:07:59,880
My temperature will keep rising.

113
00:08:04,840 --> 00:08:06,560
Then I must go.

114
00:08:06,920 --> 00:08:08,960
All you're doing is worrying.

115
00:08:10,320 --> 00:08:12,600
I like holding hands,
looking at each other,

116
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:14,480
and being happy together.

117
00:08:15,360 --> 00:08:16,800
But I don't want to be sick together.

118
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:19,920
Fine, I'll leave.

119
00:08:20,840 --> 00:08:23,240
But don't get sick again.

120
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:25,880
I'm all better now. Don't worry.

121
00:08:25,960 --> 00:08:27,680
Call me if anything happens.

122
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:31,400
Let's video call instead.

123
00:08:32,320 --> 00:08:35,280
You love me so much, don't you?

124
00:08:36,960 --> 00:08:38,919
Yes, I do.

125
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:41,840
Me too.

126
00:09:12,840 --> 00:09:13,960
Hello?

127
00:09:13,960 --> 00:09:16,120
Hello, I'm Professor Seo Hyun-jung,

128
00:09:16,120 --> 00:09:18,000
the cultural communications professor.

129
00:09:18,080 --> 00:09:19,440
Hello.

130
00:09:19,440 --> 00:09:22,280
Have you given the essay some thought?

131
00:09:25,320 --> 00:09:28,800
Things are a bit hectic for me
at the moment.

132
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:31,520
I'm sorry.

133
00:10:13,960 --> 00:10:16,880
(Professor Hwang Gab-su)

134
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:22,120
The receiver cannot be reached.
You will be directed to voicemail.

135
00:10:29,040 --> 00:10:32,240
(I think the variation is happening
in your body as well.)

136
00:11:24,800 --> 00:11:26,000
Professor Seo.

137
00:11:26,440 --> 00:11:28,120
This is Ko Mi-ran.

138
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:31,600
I'll write that essay.

139
00:11:31,720 --> 00:11:33,320
I'm glad you agreed to do so.

140
00:11:33,640 --> 00:11:36,200
May I ask what changed your mind?

141
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:37,280
There's someone...

142
00:11:37,920 --> 00:11:40,160
that I love.

143
00:11:42,440 --> 00:11:45,720
But we're in an unusual situation.

144
00:11:47,440 --> 00:11:49,360
We don't know what will happen.

145
00:11:52,640 --> 00:11:56,120
I feel like I should write down our story
to be remembered.

146
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:05,000
(At the age of 44, I found my first love.)

147
00:12:05,080 --> 00:12:07,240
(At the age of 44, I found my first love.)

148
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,320
(However...)

149
00:12:22,080 --> 00:12:24,120
(However, this could be my last.)

150
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:26,320
