566
00:43:06,920 --> 00:43:08,960
You better not call me for a while, witch.

567
00:43:08,960 --> 00:43:09,960
What?

568
00:43:10,840 --> 00:43:11,920
Gosh.

569
00:43:13,320 --> 00:43:14,960
-Honey.
-Yes?

570
00:43:14,960 --> 00:43:18,160
How about a nice bowl
of warm fish cake soup?

571
00:43:18,560 --> 00:43:20,760
We could have shots of soju
to go along with it.

572
00:43:21,840 --> 00:43:23,080
Shall we?

573
00:43:25,160 --> 00:43:26,440
Do you know a good place?

574
00:43:26,880 --> 00:43:28,480
-I know many.
-Let's go.

575
00:43:28,880 --> 00:43:31,360
What was that about? Gosh.

576
00:43:32,160 --> 00:43:33,760
I'll get going, ma'am.

577
00:43:33,760 --> 00:43:35,200
Okay.

578
00:43:36,000 --> 00:43:38,880
I thought you wanted to work here
so you could work at the station.

579
00:43:38,880 --> 00:43:40,600
Did you give up on finding a job there?

580
00:43:40,600 --> 00:43:44,000
Yes. I don't want to work
at the station anymore.

581
00:43:44,480 --> 00:43:47,280
The people there are mean and unfair.

582
00:43:48,600 --> 00:43:50,600
Thank you for everything, ma'am.

583
00:43:50,600 --> 00:43:52,800
Sure. It was nice having you.

584
00:43:54,200 --> 00:43:55,400
-Chae-yeon.
-Yes?

585
00:43:55,400 --> 00:43:57,000
You should log out from your account.

586
00:43:57,000 --> 00:43:58,920
It's okay. That's not my ID anyway.

587
00:44:03,520 --> 00:44:06,200
(Put Ko Mi-ran back
into the cryonic capsule.)

588
00:44:06,760 --> 00:44:09,040
(That's our deal.)

589
00:44:09,040 --> 00:44:11,920
(You were blinded by love
and acted too rashly.)

590
00:44:11,920 --> 00:44:15,560
(I'm considering releasing this
to the press right now.)

591
00:44:17,960 --> 00:44:19,440
Look for Professor Jo.

592
00:44:19,440 --> 00:44:20,640
He knows...

593
00:44:23,800 --> 00:44:26,000
where Lee Seok-du is.

594
00:44:27,520 --> 00:44:29,400
(I need to find Professor Hwang.)

595
00:44:29,760 --> 00:44:31,080
(I'm running out of time.)

596
00:44:34,040 --> 00:44:35,320
Please help me.

597
00:45:01,120 --> 00:45:02,360
(Na Ha-young)

598
00:45:04,600 --> 00:45:05,680
Hello?

599
00:45:06,080 --> 00:45:07,160
It's me.

600
00:45:07,680 --> 00:45:09,480
What are you trying to find out from me?

601
00:45:10,120 --> 00:45:11,880
Professor Jo is in danger.

602
00:45:11,880 --> 00:45:13,640
I called to tell you that.

603
00:45:15,760 --> 00:45:17,920
Ever since his car explosion incident,

604
00:45:18,240 --> 00:45:20,640
the police have been with him at the lab.

605
00:45:20,640 --> 00:45:22,360
That's why Lee Hyeong-du
couldn't do anything.

606
00:45:23,600 --> 00:45:25,520
Now he knows the police
aren't at the lab anymore.

607
00:45:25,520 --> 00:45:26,720
You should warn Professor Jo.

608
00:45:27,680 --> 00:45:29,080
How did he know that?

609
00:45:31,960 --> 00:45:33,080
Because I...

610
00:45:37,200 --> 00:45:39,280
Because I told him.

611
00:46:02,240 --> 00:46:03,320
It's me.

612
00:46:03,320 --> 00:46:04,400
Yes?

613
00:46:04,400 --> 00:46:06,520
Can you go to Professor Jo's lab now?

614
00:46:06,520 --> 00:46:07,640
You need to hurry.

615
00:46:52,200 --> 00:46:53,480
You, guard at the front of the lab.

616
00:46:53,480 --> 00:46:54,800
The rest of you can standby outside.

617
00:46:54,800 --> 00:46:55,880
Yes, sir.

618
00:47:02,960 --> 00:47:04,040
(Cold-hearted Punk: Don't go anywhere...
and stick right beside Professor Jo.)

619
00:47:04,040 --> 00:47:05,520
(Don't go anywhere...)
(Cold-hearted Punk: Don't go anywhere...
and stick right beside Professor Jo.)

620
00:47:05,520 --> 00:47:07,440
(and stick right beside Professor Jo.)
(Cold-hearted Punk: Don't go anywhere...
and stick right beside Professor Jo.)

621
00:47:07,600 --> 00:47:09,640
(We don't know
what kind of symptoms might show.)

622
00:47:19,280 --> 00:47:21,040
"Maito Magick"?
(Maito Magick)

623
00:47:21,600 --> 00:47:22,840
What is this?

624
00:47:23,720 --> 00:47:25,200
"Maito Magick"?

625
00:47:26,320 --> 00:47:28,200
You have my trust.

626
00:47:28,640 --> 00:47:30,880
M, 3, 4.

627
00:47:34,240 --> 00:47:35,320
M,

628
00:47:36,920 --> 00:47:38,120
3, 4.

629
00:47:45,400 --> 00:47:47,680
Maito Magick number 34.

630
00:47:59,560 --> 00:48:01,080
I've moved out of Mi-ran's house.

631
00:48:04,000 --> 00:48:07,120
I'll stay here until I find a new place.

632
00:48:07,120 --> 00:48:09,560
No. Get out.

633
00:48:14,800 --> 00:48:15,880
Dad.

634
00:48:21,680 --> 00:48:24,200
Hwang Byung-sim, Hwang Ji-hoon.

635
00:48:25,760 --> 00:48:27,680
You two must really be father and son.

636
00:48:28,120 --> 00:48:30,480
You have the same taste in women.

637
00:48:34,080 --> 00:48:36,160
I'm so embarrassed...

638
00:48:36,320 --> 00:48:37,520
to see people.

639
00:48:40,800 --> 00:48:43,600
I gave up on Mi-ran.

640
00:48:44,360 --> 00:48:45,640
The reason is,

641
00:48:46,000 --> 00:48:48,360
more than being Mi-ran's first love,

642
00:48:48,360 --> 00:48:50,880
I believe it's more valuable
to be your father.

643
00:48:50,880 --> 00:48:53,120
I compared it on a balance sheet,
and that's what I got.

644
00:48:53,120 --> 00:48:54,320
Thank you, Dad.

645
00:48:54,560 --> 00:48:56,800
Can I start dating Mi-ran now?

646
00:48:57,240 --> 00:48:59,760
-What?
-She's my type.

647
00:48:59,760 --> 00:49:01,000
You punk.

648
00:49:01,240 --> 00:49:03,080
If your father steps back
in such a cool way,

649
00:49:03,080 --> 00:49:05,360
you should say something really cool too.

650
00:49:05,360 --> 00:49:07,200
"Date her"? What are you saying?

651
00:49:07,200 --> 00:49:09,760
You didn't step back.
You were pushed back.

652
00:49:11,040 --> 00:49:13,840
No. Mi-ran is my friend.

653
00:49:13,840 --> 00:49:15,480
What's wrong with that?

654
00:49:15,600 --> 00:49:17,200
It's better than dating
the mom of a friend.

655
00:49:17,200 --> 00:49:18,240
Gosh.

656
00:49:19,120 --> 00:49:20,960
You've been interning
at the Variety Department,

657
00:49:20,960 --> 00:49:23,520
so you're making a joke?
How is that any better?

658
00:49:23,640 --> 00:49:26,400
How is it any different?
A friend's mom versus Mom's friend?

659
00:49:26,800 --> 00:49:28,080
That's not what I mean.

660
00:49:28,080 --> 00:49:29,440
Both of you, shut your mouths!

661
00:49:29,760 --> 00:49:30,920
I won't allow it.

662
00:49:30,920 --> 00:49:33,240
Gosh. It's Dong-chan's fault.

663
00:49:33,400 --> 00:49:35,640
I'm sure he ruined you.

664
00:49:35,640 --> 00:49:38,680
Mi-ran has a boyfriend.

665
00:50:06,400 --> 00:50:07,880
You two should go home.

666
00:50:08,000 --> 00:50:10,120
I'll finish this
even if I have to stay up all night.

667
00:50:10,400 --> 00:50:11,920
I'll be in touch, Mr. Ma.

668
00:50:12,160 --> 00:50:13,240
Okay.

669
00:50:27,280 --> 00:50:28,480
Sweet dreams.

670
00:50:29,720 --> 00:50:30,840
You too, honey.

671
00:50:33,240 --> 00:50:34,240
"Honey"...

672
00:50:34,680 --> 00:50:35,920
I'll pick you up tomorrow morning.

673
00:50:37,480 --> 00:50:39,960
I'll go with Dad tomorrow.

674
00:50:39,960 --> 00:50:41,000
Why?

675
00:50:41,000 --> 00:50:42,760
He wants to do it.

676
00:50:43,880 --> 00:50:45,040
All right.

677
00:50:45,600 --> 00:50:46,760
You should hurry home.

678
00:50:46,760 --> 00:50:48,880
After we resolve things one by one,

679
00:50:48,880 --> 00:50:51,440
we'll be able to live
just like ordinary people.

680
00:50:51,840 --> 00:50:54,240
After we take the reagent
and find Professor Hwang again,

681
00:50:54,600 --> 00:50:56,840
we just need to get the treatment
to get our temperatures normal.

682
00:50:57,960 --> 00:50:58,960
You're right.

683
00:51:00,640 --> 00:51:01,640
See you, then.

684
00:51:35,560 --> 00:51:38,800
But this antidote
hasn't gone through a clinical trial.

685
00:51:40,080 --> 00:51:42,920
So one person
needs to get the injection first.

686
00:51:45,560 --> 00:51:48,200
I'll get the injection first.

687
00:51:49,320 --> 00:51:51,360
If I turn out to be fine,

688
00:51:52,000 --> 00:51:53,360
you can give it to him.

689
00:51:59,880 --> 00:52:02,360
Hey, Professor Jo. I'll be on my way soon.

690
00:52:02,560 --> 00:52:04,000
Is Mi-ran there already?

691
00:52:04,480 --> 00:52:06,280
Yes, she's here. But the thing is,

692
00:52:07,240 --> 00:52:10,200
Mi-ran already got the injection.

693
00:52:12,440 --> 00:52:13,480
What?

694
00:52:36,040 --> 00:52:37,640
It's been two hours since she got it.

695
00:52:37,960 --> 00:52:39,400
I think the antidote works.

696
00:52:43,560 --> 00:52:44,960
Why did you get the injection first?

697
00:52:47,200 --> 00:52:49,160
Because I wanted to live first.

698
00:52:49,720 --> 00:52:52,720
Why do you always do everything first?

699
00:53:27,880 --> 00:53:31,800
This reminds me of the day
I first met you guys 20 years ago.

700
00:53:32,160 --> 00:53:34,080
For 20 years,

701
00:53:34,680 --> 00:53:36,920
you guys were frozen and asleep.

702
00:53:37,760 --> 00:53:40,360
But on the other hand,
I've seen you guys for 20 years.

703
00:53:40,920 --> 00:53:43,200
I guess that's why I'm not surprised
to see that you're dating.

704
00:53:45,320 --> 00:53:47,600
I guess we were meant to be.

705
00:53:49,720 --> 00:53:51,640
We were destined to be with each other.

706
00:54:14,800 --> 00:54:16,400
You both need to keep this in mind.

707
00:54:16,880 --> 00:54:18,640
This is just an antidote.

708
00:54:18,640 --> 00:54:20,760
It's not a cure that will bring
your body temperature back.

709
00:54:21,040 --> 00:54:25,440
You both need to keep maintaining
a body temperature of 31.5℃.

710
